  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Depressed patients unremitted after monotherapy with citalopram or bupropion will remit
      following six weeks treatment with the combination of citalopram and bupropion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Participants in another study who did not remit during 12 weeks treatment with citalopram (to
      40 mg/d) or bupropion (to 450 mg/d) will have citalopram (to 40 mg/d) or bupropion (to 450
      mg/d) added for six weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
